title: How did patients feel about how quickly they received care from out-of-hours GP service?
analysis_commentary: Overall the majority (greater than 60%) of patients thought the time it took to receive care from the out-of-hours GP service was about right. However, there has been a slight decrease from 63% in 2011/12 to 62% in 2012/13, with initial figures for January to September 2013 continuing this trend with 60%.
